    "original_goal": "Migrate 3-phase PWM motor control to new AURIX target (TC387 → TC4D7) using eGTM ATOM and unified PWM driver.",
    "functional_behavior": "Generate 3-phase U/V/W PWM at 20 kHz, center-aligned (SOMP), complementary outputs via CDTM with HS active-high and LS active-low, 1 µs symmetric deadtime, synchronous start and shadow-update at period event, period ISR on cpu0 (prio 20), and duty updates scheduled from STM ticks.",
    "technical_approach": "Use unified high-level IfxEgtm_Pwm on TC4xx with ATOM submodule and CDTM. Configure eGTM clocks (FXCLK0, DTM CLK0), map ATOM TOUT pins via IfxEgtm_PinMap, configure complementary pairs and deadtime in IfxEgtm_Pwm, start channels synchronously, install a period-event ISR that calls IfxEgtm_Pwm_interruptHandler, and update duties using IfxEgtm_Pwm_updateChannelsDuty (shadow) from an STM-driven scheduler."
