    "context_preserved": "The unified IfxEgtm_Pwm on TC4xx is used to realize 3-phase, 20 kHz, center-aligned PWM with complementary outputs and 1 µs deadtime via CDTM, synchronous start and shadow updates at period, ISR on cpu0 for housekeeping and duty synchronization, and STM-based duty scheduling—matching the original TC387 TOM-based intent while adapting to eGTM ATOM on TC4D7. Notes: verify TOUT-to-pin availability in IfxEgtm_PinMap for KIT_A3G_TC4D7_LITE (P02.0/P02.1 macros indicate EGTM ATOM0_0/0N; proposed EGTM1.ATOM1 CH0–5 must be cross-checked). Configure FXCLK0 and DTM CLK0 at 100 MHz using IfxEgtm_Cmu and IfxEgtm_Dtm. Install interruptEgtmAtomPeriod on cpu0 (prio 20) and call IfxEgtm_Pwm_interruptHandler in the ISR. Use IfxStm/IfxStm_Timer to generate 1 ms ticks to compute and queue new duties."
